      {
        "id": "sec_2",
        "document_id": "95b06e93627aab6fcdfb83214bda2acd",
        "title": "2.  Policy rationale for and issues with tax expenditures",
        "level": 1,
        "page_start": 7,
        "page_end": 8,
        "child_sections": [],
        "key_entities": [],
        "summary": "The Ethiopian government employs tax expenditures, such as tax holidays and credits, to stimulate investment in the manufacturing sector and enhance domestic production capacity, ultimately aiming to boost economic development and improve living standards. Various incentive packages are available for investors and exporters, including duty-free imports of capital goods and tax privileges for exporters. Additionally, the Ministry of Finance provides ad hoc exemptions to stabilize prices of certain commodities and support local industries, with the overarching goals of promoting investment, technology transfer, and equitable investment distribution across regions.",
        "data_types_present": [
          "paragraphs"
        ],
