      {
        "id": "sec_3",
        "document_id": "95b06e93627aab6fcdfb83214bda2acd",
        "title": "3.  Definitions and data",
        "level": 1,
        "page_start": 9,
        "page_end": 15,
        "child_sections": [],
        "key_entities": [],
        "summary": "This section defines the benchmark tax system, which serves as a reference point for estimating tax expenditures, specifically focusing on positive import tax expenditures where importers pay lower customs duties than the benchmark rates. It emphasizes that the benchmark includes standard tax rates from relevant regulations, as well as specific exemptions and agreements, while also addressing the treatment of negative tax expenditures. The report analyzes lower rates and exemptions separately, particularly for customs duties, including preferential rates for local manufacturers.",
