      {
        "id": "sec_10",
        "document_id": "95b06e93627aab6fcdfb83214bda2acd",
        "title": "4.3  Excise duty",
        "level": 1,
        "page_start": 27,
        "page_end": 32,
        "child_sections": [],
        "key_entities": [],
        "summary": "The section discusses excise duty expenditures in Ethiopia, highlighting a significant increase to ETB 18.8 billion in FY 2020/21, up 117% from the previous fiscal year. Direct effects accounted for ETB 15.8 billion (84.1% of total expenditures), while indirect effects through VAT and surtax rose to nearly ETB 3 billion, significantly higher than previous years. The surge in expenditures was primarily driven by a substantial increase in statutory excise tax liability on vehicle imports.",
