      {
        "id": "sec_11",
        "document_id": "95b06e93627aab6fcdfb83214bda2acd",
        "title": "4.4  VAT",
        "level": 1,
        "page_start": 33,
        "page_end": 35,
        "child_sections": [],
        "key_entities": [],
        "summary": "The section discusses VAT tax expenditures in Ethiopia, highlighting that forgone VAT amounted to ETB 44.6 billion in FY 2020/21, with 94.7% attributed to direct effects and 5.3% to indirect effects through surtax. This represents a 26% increase from the previous fiscal year, with expenditures rising from ETB 35 billion in FY 2019/20 and ETB 44 billion in FY 2018/19. It also notes that the actual fiscal cost may be lower due to higher import VAT leading to increased domestic VAT collections.",
