        "document_id": "95b06e93627aab6fcdfb83214bda2acd",
        "title": "4.5  Surtax",
        "level": 1,
        "page_start": 36,
        "page_end": 40,
        "child_sections": [],
        "key_entities": [],
        "summary": "The section discusses surtax expenditures in Ethiopia, which totaled ETB 18.4 billion in FY 2020/21, marking a 68% increase from ETB 11 billion in FY 2019/20. Surtax expenditures accounted for 0.4% of GDP, 3.3% of imports, and 15.3% of all import tax expenditures in FY 2020/21, indicating a growing significance in the tax structure compared to previous years. The document notes that surtax does not indirectly affect the collection of other taxes, as it is applied last in the calculation of border taxes.",
